Dangers of low or high estrogen levels

Estrogen is truly a wonderful thing that gives us smooth skin and a curvy figure, but is it really true that the higher the level, the better?
1Dangers of excessive estrogen

Accelerate bone closure

Estrogen promotes bone closure in children, and once the bones close, height will basically stop increasing. Therefore, for children who are still growing, excessively high levels of estrogen can indeed affect their height.

Uterine fibroids

Estrogen not only stimulates the growth of endometrial tissue, but also the growth of smooth muscle. Excessive estrogen levels can also lead to uterine fibroids to some extent.

Promotes the development, recurrence, and metastasis of breast cancer.

Most breast diseases are caused by excessively high estrogen levels and endocrine disorders.

Estrogen is a precious hormone that accompanies a woman throughout her life, but too low a level is certainly not good.

Inducing depression

Studies have found that whether it is menopausal depression or postpartum depression, most patients with depression also have a lack of estrogen.

Menstrual irregularities, or even premature menopause

The combined action of estrogen and progesterone creates a regular menstrual cycle. If estrogen levels are too low, the menstrual cycle will inevitably become irregular. Severe estrogen deficiency may lead to female infertility.

Skin deterioration

Low estrogen levels can cause women's skin to lose elasticity, become dull, dry, and develop various pigmentation issues.

Menopausal syndrome

The gradual decline in ovarian function and the gradual decrease in estrogen levels are the causes of menopausal syndrome in women.

